OL,3,CMen accused of taking part in violent
OL,4,Cdisorder in Hartlepool appear in court
OL,6,FPaul Doney, prosecuting, said around
OL,7,F200 people gathered on Wednesday in
OL,8,Fthe town centre and police were
OL,9,Fdeployed to maintain order.
OL,11,FThe march moved towards mosques and a
OL,12,Fcommunity centre, Mr Doney said, and
OL,13,Fofficers came under attack from
OL,14,Fbricks, eggs and other weapons.
OL,16,FDisorder lasted for several hours and
OL,17,Fa police car was torched, the
OL,18,Fprosecution said.
