OL,6,FMailen was "constantly in the face of
OL,7,Fofficers" and was gesticulating
OL,8,Ftowards them, shouting, until he was
OL,9,Fstruck on the leg by an officer's
OL,10,Fextendable baton.
OL,12,FHis partner Sheers, who wept during
OL,13,Fthe hearing, was then bitten on the
OL,14,Fhip by a police dog, the court heard.
OL,16,FHe had been trying to push through the
OL,17,Fpolice cordon, shouting and refusing
OL,18,Fto move away.
